@database HELP
@node MAIN
@title "AmigaGuideź Help"
   I.    @{" Buttons " link HELP_BUTTONS}
   II.   @{" Menus " link HELP_MENUS}
   III.  @{" Keystrokes " link HELP_KEYSTROKES}
   IV.   @{" Arrow Keys " link HELP_ARROWS}
   V.    @{" Function Keys " link HELP_FUNCTION}
   VI.   @{" Environment Variables " Link HELP_VARS}

note: gmigaguide sometimes has problems with the screenupdate
      please select the size gadget in the right lower corner
      and resize the screen to get a update.
@endnode

@node HELP_VARS "AmigaGuideź Help: Environment Variables"

Use the DOS command, SetEnv to set any of the following variables.

 AmigaGuide/Path
  This variable contains the list of path names that AmigaGuideź
  should search through when it attempts to open a database.

  For example:

    SetEnv AmigaGuide/Path "Workbench:Autodocs Workbench:Includes"


 AmigaGuide/Pens
  Gives you control over the colors that AmigaGuideź uses to
  render the text and link points with.

    SetEnv AmigaGuide/Pens <abcdefgh>

  where:

    a = Background pen
    b = Button text pen
    c = Button background pen
    d = Highlighted button text pen
    e = Highlighted button background pen
    f = Outline pen
    g = Highlight outline pen
    h = Text on background pen

  For example:

    SetEnv AmigaGuide/Pens 21213001
    SetEnv AmigaGuide/Text BOLD

  will give a very sharp look.

 AmigaGuide/Text
  Enables you to determine what the link points look like.

    SetEnv AmigaGuide/Text <style>

  where style can be one of the following:

    BUTTON
    HIGHLIGHT
    UNDERLINE
    BOLD
    ITALIC
@endnode

@node HELP_BUTTONS "AmigaGuideź Help: Buttons"
 Contents
  Display the Table of Contents document for the current database.

 Index
  Display the index document for the current database.

 Help
  Display the help document for the current database.  If the
  database doesn't have a Help document of its own, then the
  global Help database will be used instead.

 Retrace
  Go back to the previous node.

 Browse
  Step through the documents in sequential order, in the order
  they appear in the database.

@endnode

@node HELP_MENUS "AmigaGuideź Help: Menus"
Project

 Print
  Print the current document.

 Print As...
  Select the output device to use when printing.

 Close Window
  Close the active document window.

 Quit
  Close all windows for the current database, and exit.

Edit

 Mark
  Start marking a block of text for copying to the clipboard.

 Copy
  Copy the current document to the clipboard.

 Annotate...
  Add custom notes to a document.

Navigation

 Next Page
  Scroll forwards a page.

 Previous Page
  Scroll backwards a page.

 Find Document...
  Locate a document.
@endnode
@node HELP_KEYSTROKES
@title "AmigaGuideź Help: Keystrokes"
 TAB
  Cycle forward through the buttons.

 Shift TAB
  Cycle backwards through the buttons.

 HELP
  Display this document in its own window.

 ESC
  Close the active AmigaGuideź window.

 Backspace
  Scroll backwards a page.

 RETURN
  Activate the default button (the highlighted one).

 SPACE
  Scroll forwards a page.

 >
  Go to the end of the current document.

 <
  Go to the beginning of the current document.
@endnode
@node HELP_ARROWS
@title "AmigaGuideź Help: Arrow Keys"
 Up
  Scroll up through the document.

 Down
  Scroll down through the document.

 Shift-Up
  Go up a page in the document.

 Shift-Down
  Go down a page in the document.

 Alt-Up
  Go to the beginning of the document.

 Alt-Down
  Go to the end of the document.
@endnode
@node HELP_FUNCTION
@title "AmigaGuideź Help: Function Keys"
 F6
  Table of Contents.

 F9
  Activate Next Window.

 F10
  Cycle active AmigaGuideź window front to back.
@endnode
